gujarati.context:
Dama vinā darshanānī, Chūṭi tē na kare chēk;
Āśhā tajī muni antarē, Pachī karyō ēm vivēka.

To:

Without seeing the place, the wanderer does not depart; 
The desires dwindle in the heart of the wise one, and then such discernment arises.

Here is the translation:

I came how, got rough; I ponder in my mind only;
Vasudeva bound Devaki, made a play Lila come here.

Here is the translation:

Taking such a weapon in hand, Dwarika's sight by hand; 
With love-possessed Munis seen, sorrowful to know and not to be moved.

Here is the translation:

This I told Munine to Bhagwan, then it has become inner wisdom;
Munin thought in his mind, and then beheld Guru's mercy.

Seetha Swapnamama Laadilo Lal, Rama Sahit Jaata Varatal;
Bolya Paraspar Parabhat, Kahi Swapnani Guruane Vat.

Note: The above response is a direct translation of the Gujarati couplet without any added words.

Here is the translation:

Done festival preparation, took horses' playfulness; 
With folded hands on left side, got good people's company with a lot.

Sudi ekadasi vartala, aavya naath saath laa meral;
Aavya te di ja Dwarkanaath, Raani Rukmini laa saath.

It is eleven days of Chaitra month, I have taken the path with you; 
I have come to this day, the Lord of Dwarka has taken me and my queen Rukmini with him.

Here is the translation:

The festival done, heavy with flowers and music, I have celebrated my guru's master; 
From Dwarka we went, whoever goes to Mathura, all gods come together at one pilgrimage.

Ramnavmiye puja kari, Vimla ekadashi archyaha Hari;
Tiyan jay jay bole che jan, dekhii dushtonaa daaiyaan man.

Worship is done on Ram Navmi, and Hare worshiped on Ekadasi;
They chant "Victory to God" over there, and see the wicked ones in their mind.

Here is the translation:

Only in my presence difficulties go away, many people see; 
It starts with being wild there, only then do people worship me again and again, so many times.

Here is the translation:

Take Hare's hand, play colorful with friends without a leader;
Keep true to your vow, sing sweet melodies, dance with people, and be blessed.
